ead (not in MVP-1).","why_it_can_fail":null},{"label":"Balance-sheet safety","value":null,"unit":"","status":"na","read":null,"meaning":"A bank is structurally levered (deposits are its raw material); D/E & interest-cover don't apply.","why_useful":"Read bank safety from capital adequacy (CAR) and NPAs instead (not in MVP-1).","why_it_can_fail":null},{"label":"Earnings momentum","value":1.05,"unit":"% YoY","status":"ok","read":"Profit up 1% YoY \u2014 modest.","meaning":"Trailing-twelve-month net profit vs the year-ago TTM (and whether the YoY rate is rising = 'accelerating').","why_useful":"Improving, accelerating earnings tend to drive re-rating; falling profit warns of a deteriorating business.","why_it_can_fail":"TTM can be lumpy for cyclicals/one-offs; cross-check the multi-year trend on the Fundamentals tab."}]},"valuation":{"ok":true,"is_bank":true,"pe_now":6.8,"pe_percentile":57.0,"median_pe":6.4,"earnings_yield_pct":14.71,"pb":1.14,"ev_ebitda":null,"quality_score":32.0,"pat_cagr_5y_pct":46.1,"peg":0.15,"cheapness":{"status":"ok","read":"P/E at the 57-percentile of its 10-yr range \u2014 mid-range vs its own history."},"expectations":"At 6.8\u00d7 earnings for ~46% 5-yr profit CAGR, the market is paying \u22480.15\u00d7 growth (PEG). >2 = a lot already priced in; <1 = cheap if growth holds. This PEG divides TTM P/E by TRAILING 5-year annual PAT CAGR (endpoint-to-endpoint) \u2014 a time-axis mismatch vs the textbook FORWARD-EPS PEG, and one abnormal base/terminal year distorts the CAGR. A rough trailing valuation-vs-growth gauge, not a precise forward PEG.","cyclical_caveat":null,"meaning":"P/E percentile = where today's price-to-earnings sits within the stock's own last-10-yr range (low = cheap vs its past). Paired with the Quality score and 5-yr profit growth so a cheap multiple is judged against business strength, not in isolation.","why_useful":"Cheapness only matters relative to quality and growth \u2014 a low P/E on a declining or peak-cyclical business